Pours very thick with nice tan head. Aroma is hop forward with rich roasted finish. Mouthfeel and flavor are all a step up. Nothing to complain about here; far better than your average imperial stout.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Found at my local Hy-Vee. Served only slightly cooled. It seems to pour thin and with minimal head. Appearances are deceiving, however, as the rich roasted flavor starts with a nice amount of hops. The finish is smooth and the mouthfeel belies the thin lacing. As good as advertised and not to be missed on a cold winter's night.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
